article.headline: Austin Peay 73, Jacksonville St. 58
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Todd Babington scored 19 points, including 13 in the second half, to lead Austin Peay to its ninth straight win with a 73-58 victory over Jacksonville State on Thursday night. Austin Peay (12-6, 9-1 Ohio Valley Conference) got its sixth straight win at home with help from Drake Reed with 16 points, Wes Channels with 12 and Landon Shipley with 10. Jacksonville State (5-15, 3-8) took a 31-28 lead early in the second half on a layup by Courtney Bradley, who had a game-high 22 points and seven rebounds before fouling out. Eric Smith added 20 points, including 10-of-12 free throws. But the Governors shot 50 percent from the field for the half, with the bench adding 26 points to the Gamecocks' 10. Austin Peay also took advantage of 24 turnovers to score 26 points. Babington was 6-of-10 from the field, including 4-of-8 from 3-point range. The Governors led the boards 40-36, despite a game-high 11 rebounds from the Gamecocks' Amadou Mbodji.
